      <scopecontent id="ref7">
         <head>Description of the Collection</head>
         <p>Collection includes articles, photocopied historical sources, notes, programs, booklets, correspondence, photographs, and a draft of her manuscript on the history of Stanford Memorial Church. Subjects include its mosaics by Salviati and Company, its stained glass windows by Frederick S. Lamb, and several of its pastors. Of note are the original "conditions of competition for Memorial Church" by Charles E. Hodges, 1898; a genealogy of the descendants of John D. McGilvray (stone mason and contractor who worked on the Church); and a typescript account by the Rev. D. Elton Trueblood of his Stanford years.</p>
      </scopecontent>
